==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: methanol
<hw>methanol</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The simplest
alcohol of the paraffin series, <chform>CH3.OH</chform>; methyl alcohol.
Called also <altname>wood alcohol</altname>. It is used as an antifreeze
solvent, as a fuel, and as a denaturant for ethyl alcohol.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> methyl alcohol, wood alcohol, wood spirit.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

